The life expectancy of patients with cystic fibrosis (CF) has steadily increased 
over recent decades with a corresponding increase in the frequency of 
complications of the disease. Radiologists are increasingly involved with 
managing and identifying the pulmonary complications of CF. This article reviews 
the common manifestations of CF lung disease as well as updating radiologists 
